":"heading","text":"Declaring a test function"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To declare a test function, write a Swift function declaration that does not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take any arguments, then prefix its name with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"text":" attribute:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Test func foodTruckExists() {","  \/\/ Test logic goes here.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This test function can be present at file scope or within a type. A type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"containing test functions is automatically a ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"test suite"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be optionally"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotated with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Suite"},{"text":" attribute. For more information about suites, see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/OrganizingTests"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, while this function is a valid test function, it does not actually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perform any action or test any code. To check for expected values and outcomes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in test functions, add "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Expectations","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"expectations"}],"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"expectations"},{"type":"text","text":" to the test function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Customizing a test’s name","anchor":"Customizing-a-tests-name","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To customize a test function’s name as p